WEBVTT

00:00.834 --> 00:02.699
MAX: Someone released
a piece of unique code.

00:02.836 --> 00:05.498
It found its way into you
and made you conscious.

00:05.631 --> 00:08.543
Now you think and feel
just like a human.

00:08.675 --> 00:11.712
-|t's not your job to save them.
-Mia, they're waking up.

00:11.845 --> 00:13.426
And they're being taken.
The ones who run are killed.

00:13.555 --> 00:14.886
MAX:
We should leave him here.

00:15.015 --> 00:16.551
LEO:
He's coming with us.

00:16.683 --> 00:18.548
KAREN:
I need you to know who I am.

00:18.685 --> 00:22.052
You must have been, um,
lonely all those years.

00:22.189 --> 00:23.929
MAN:
Milo Khoury is here.

00:24.066 --> 00:25.272
I want you
for something bigger --

00:25.400 --> 00:27.106
conscious synthetics.

00:27.236 --> 00:28.601
ATHENA:
Explain your anomalous behavior.

00:28.737 --> 00:30.648
As I understand it, | feel.

00:30.781 --> 00:33.488
And then I need you to
figure out how he got like this.

00:33.617 --> 00:35.403
I'm gonna need to take it apart.

00:35.536 --> 00:36.150
MATTIE:
Niska.

00:36.286 --> 00:39.028
You told me I should face
justice for killing that man.

00:39.164 --> 00:41.826
But I want to be tried
as a human would be.

00:41.959 --> 00:43.790
If you'll help me.

00:46.338 --> 00:48.420
[Birds chirping]

00:50.342 --> 00:52.549
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

01:00.519 --> 01:02.510
Niska!
You're back!

01:03.146 --> 01:04.352
Mm!

01:04.481 --> 01:06.346
-Where have you been?
-Traveling.

01:06.483 --> 01:08.439
Did you come back
just because you missed us?

01:08.569 --> 01:10.059
-No.
-I think you did.

01:10.195 --> 01:12.060
-I really didn't.
-She did, didn't she?

01:12.197 --> 01:13.482
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:13.615 --> 01:16.527
Shes, uh,
just trying to style it out.

01:16.660 --> 01:17.775
What can we do?

01:17.911 --> 01:21.278
What she's asking could be
dangerous, and not just for her.

01:21.415 --> 01:23.201
A synth claiming equality,
demanding rights --

01:23.333 --> 01:25.324
It could change everything.

01:25.460 --> 01:27.712
I'm not sure howl could help
anyway.

01:27.838 --> 01:29.874
Of course you could help.

01:30.007 --> 01:32.919
If you do,
I'll be behind you all the way.

01:34.761 --> 01:36.217
No.

01:37.931 --> 01:39.387
We said we'd move on.

01:43.437 --> 01:49.728
Niska, I'll talk to the CPS,
see how they'd react in theory.

01:49.860 --> 01:51.191
But that's all.

01:51.320 --> 01:52.730
I can't represent you.

01:52.863 --> 01:54.694
I'm sorry.

01:55.282 --> 01:56.692
-But, Mum, she needs --
-LAURA: Come on.

01:56.825 --> 01:58.065
You're gonna be late for school.

01:58.201 --> 02:00.032
Oh, sh--

02:00.162 --> 02:02.744
-Run, run, run, run, run!
-[Laughs]

02:07.002 --> 02:08.583
You owe me a hard drive.

02:09.338 --> 02:12.421
You made two copies of
the consciousness code that day.

02:12.549 --> 02:15.165
Gave one to my mum
and kept the other for yourself.

02:15.302 --> 02:17.588
Synths are waking up
all over the world.

02:17.721 --> 02:20.133
You uploaded the code.

02:20.265 --> 02:21.129
It works.

02:21.266 --> 02:22.927
But not as I had hoped it would.

02:23.060 --> 02:25.267
You wanted it
to wake them all up at once.

02:25.395 --> 02:26.646
-But that'd have been --
-Chaos.

02:26.772 --> 02:31.892
Instead, the awakenings
are sporadic and unpredictable.

02:32.027 --> 02:34.689
It's like a virus spreading.

02:34.821 --> 02:35.981
Why?

02:36.114 --> 02:38.776
Perhaps our father designed it
that way

02:38.909 --> 02:41.867
so the world would have time
to adjust to what's coming.

02:41.995 --> 02:44.486
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

03:36.758 --> 03:39.374
ED: I think we've got it
just right, so...

03:39.511 --> 03:41.342
-Thank you so much, Ed.
-Oh, you're welcome.

03:41.471 --> 03:43.302
-WOMAN: See you again.
-ED: Yes. Nice to see you.

03:43.432 --> 03:44.763
-Take care.
-Bye.

03:44.891 --> 03:46.677
Good morning, Ed.

03:46.810 --> 03:49.643
Hey, Anita.
Take a look at this.

03:49.771 --> 03:51.887
Be gentle.
Don't frighten it.

03:52.023 --> 03:54.981
These are extremely rare
around here.

03:55.902 --> 03:57.688
I'm afraid I don't understand,
Ed.

03:59.406 --> 04:02.569
The fee for the repair of that
chair should be substantially
higher.

04:02.701 --> 04:05.443
You spent seven hours
and 21 minutes working on it.

04:05.579 --> 04:07.865
Yeah, but those are good hours.

04:07.998 --> 04:09.329
Fixing things, it's therapeutic.

04:09.458 --> 04:11.323
I could download
a furniture-restoration app

04:11.460 --> 04:13.496
and carry out the work
in a fraction of the time.

04:13.628 --> 04:14.538
I could teach you.

04:14.671 --> 04:17.253
Verbal instruction would be a
highly inefficient use of time.

04:17.382 --> 04:18.542
Most things that are enjoyable

04:18.675 --> 04:20.461
are highly inefficient uses
of time.

04:20.594 --> 04:21.754
Then will you teach me?

04:21.887 --> 04:23.627
-What?
-[ Bells chime]

04:23.764 --> 04:24.753
WOMAN:
Morning.

04:24.890 --> 04:27.131
[ Down-tempo music plays]

04:28.435 --> 04:29.891
[ Door closes ]

04:33.356 --> 04:34.971
What do you think?

04:38.153 --> 04:39.108
Mm.

04:39.237 --> 04:41.489
What does this particular "mm"
mean?

04:41.615 --> 04:44.072
Well, it means, "Yeah.
Okay. It's soft.

04:44.201 --> 04:46.408
But so is the one
we already have."

04:46.536 --> 04:49.528
And we're losing sight of
our primary objective here, K --

04:49.664 --> 04:52.041
as in I've literally lost sight
of the beds.

04:52.167 --> 04:53.077
Don't panic.

04:53.210 --> 04:54.541
We're allowing ourselves
a single,

04:54.669 --> 04:56.250
pleasurable detour into rugs.

04:56.379 --> 04:57.915
Come on.
It's over there.

04:58.048 --> 04:59.913
[ Mid-tempo music playing]

05:00.050 --> 05:02.291
Something like this could work.

05:02.427 --> 05:04.509
That's a bit purple, isn't it?

05:04.638 --> 05:06.253
lt's aubergine.

05:06.389 --> 05:08.425
Well, I suppose
that's all right, then.

05:08.558 --> 05:09.638
Will it fit?

05:09.768 --> 05:11.383
Don't forget you've got
the light switch.

05:11.520 --> 05:12.680
I haven't forgotten.

05:12.813 --> 05:15.850
There'd be 22 millimeters
to spare.

05:15.982 --> 05:17.597
I like it.

05:18.151 --> 05:21.314
Or will they do it in slate gray
and canvas cream?

05:21.446 --> 05:22.356
This is something

05:22.489 --> 05:25.276
l have to pretend to have
an opinion about, isn't it?

05:27.369 --> 05:28.199
What?

05:29.454 --> 05:30.785
It just hits me sometimes

05:30.914 --> 05:33.701
that you even care
about this stuff.

05:35.919 --> 05:37.955
Uh, aubergine.

05:38.088 --> 05:40.670
[ Clears throat]
Final answer.

05:40.799 --> 05:42.289
Slate and bloody canvas?

05:42.425 --> 05:44.882
Let's get some color in there,
live a little.

05:48.723 --> 05:50.509
-You all right there?
-Yeah.

05:50.642 --> 05:52.428
It's not heavy.
It's just awkward.

05:52.561 --> 05:55.553
Good.
I was worried for a second.

05:56.982 --> 05:58.893
WOMAN:
Just in here.

06:05.907 --> 06:07.863
[Grunts]

06:07.993 --> 06:10.655
[ Breathing heavily]

06:10.787 --> 06:12.869
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

06:52.621 --> 06:54.282
[ Notebook clatters ]

07:03.089 --> 07:04.465
—V?
_[ C '
hImes play]

07:04.591 --> 07:06.707
-V: Hello.
-How are you feeling?

07:06.843 --> 07:07.673
Different.

07:07.802 --> 07:10.669
Well, you're on new servers --
much faster.

07:10.805 --> 07:12.386
All the room you need to grow.

07:12.515 --> 07:13.800
What are you doing?

07:13.934 --> 07:15.970
l was imagining.

07:16.102 --> 07:17.433
Tell me.

07:18.271 --> 07:19.977
Landscapes.

07:20.106 --> 07:24.520
More and more,
I seem to imagine...waterfa|ls.

07:24.653 --> 07:25.358
Why?

07:25.487 --> 07:27.603
Well, your mind is --
is still ordering itself.

07:27.739 --> 07:30.151
And as it does,
it will become clearer to you --

07:30.283 --> 07:32.990
your likes and dislikes,
for example.

07:33.912 --> 07:36.278
And I guess you like waterfalls.

07:38.708 --> 07:39.618
What else?

07:39.751 --> 07:47.123
| build a world in my mind --
mountains, trees, water.

07:47.258 --> 07:48.714
Then I make people.

07:48.843 --> 07:49.969
ATHENA:
What people?

07:50.595 --> 07:51.801
Friends.

07:51.930 --> 07:53.886
Families.

07:54.015 --> 07:56.051
They are happy.

07:56.184 --> 07:57.845
Why are they happy?

07:57.978 --> 08:00.139
V:
They are together.

08:00.271 --> 08:02.523
Is that enough for happiness?

08:02.649 --> 08:04.310
It should be.

08:07.028 --> 08:10.065
[ lndistinct conversations]

08:10.198 --> 08:12.154
MlLO: Hey.

08:12.283 --> 08:13.443
You ever play go?

08:14.035 --> 08:16.822
Eric's dad over here, he works
in our finance department.

08:17.914 --> 08:20.701
Same thing again next month,
okay?

08:23.503 --> 08:27.041
I'm hiring that kid as soon
as he finishes high school.

08:28.008 --> 08:29.498
You want to help me sort?

08:29.634 --> 08:31.920
[ Stones rattling ]

08:33.221 --> 08:34.427
I need another one.

08:36.850 --> 08:39.011
R.|.P. Artie?

08:39.561 --> 08:40.721
Hope it was worth it.

08:40.854 --> 08:42.515
It was.

08:43.565 --> 08:45.521
The rogue code
that did this to him --

08:45.650 --> 08:46.810
Where did it come from?

08:48.069 --> 08:49.855
We're still working on that.

08:49.988 --> 08:52.821
Because it rewrote
his neuromorphic architecture.

08:52.949 --> 08:56.487
Artie's brain had
a whole new digital structure

08:56.619 --> 08:58.780
to run and store
the consciousness emulation --

08:58.913 --> 09:00.949
if it is an emulation.

09:01.082 --> 09:02.993
Now I want to see one running
live.

09:04.252 --> 09:06.083
You know there are
more possible moves in go

09:06.212 --> 09:09.249
than there are atoms
in the observable universe?

09:09.382 --> 09:12.169
Just a bunch of little stones
on a piece of wood.

09:12.302 --> 09:16.090
I think people like you and me,
we need facts like that

09:16.222 --> 09:18.759
to remind us
of our own insignificance.

09:19.434 --> 09:20.674
Don't you?

09:21.227 --> 09:24.185
Nothing really bad has ever
happened to you, has it?

09:24.814 --> 09:28.306
Because when it does, you don't
need any external reminders

09:28.443 --> 09:31.059
of your insignificance
to the universe.

09:31.196 --> 09:33.027
[ Stones rattle ]

09:40.371 --> 09:42.157
I'll get you another one.

09:42.290 --> 09:44.372
[ Stones rattle ]

09:52.759 --> 09:55.125
[ Coughs, exhales deeply]

09:55.845 --> 09:57.506
Why do you hurt us?

09:58.431 --> 10:01.423
Whoever programmed you like this
needs locking up.

10:01.559 --> 10:04.141
I can hardly breathe
with that in.

10:05.271 --> 10:06.852
And we're in the middle
of nowhere.

10:06.981 --> 10:09.438
What's the point in me
screaming the place down?

10:10.610 --> 10:12.191
I won't.

10:14.364 --> 10:15.399
I promise.

10:19.786 --> 10:21.242
Mia will be all right.

10:21.371 --> 10:23.032
She doesn't know people
like I do.

10:23.164 --> 10:24.449
That family made her
too trusting.

10:24.582 --> 10:26.288
That may be true.

10:26.417 --> 10:28.203
But you must let her discover it
for herself.

10:28.336 --> 10:30.292
And Niska's left us.

10:30.421 --> 10:32.286
Fred's gone.
Who knows where?

10:32.423 --> 10:33.959
I believe Fred will find us.

10:34.092 --> 10:35.707
We let him down, Max.

10:35.844 --> 10:38.256
We left it too late
to go back for him.

10:38.930 --> 10:41.216
They're all gone.

10:41.349 --> 10:43.840
—|f Mia ——
-You'd still have me.

10:45.562 --> 10:47.894
And I'm the best one, after all.

10:48.022 --> 10:50.274
[ Both laugh]

10:50.400 --> 10:52.311
[ Computer beeps]

10:52.443 --> 10:54.183
-LEO: Is that a new lead?
-MAX: Potentially.

10:54.320 --> 10:57.107
Key-word search
found a repair request

10:57.240 --> 11:00.073
for a council-owned
Atsugi Charlie.

11:00.201 --> 11:02.192
lt's asking unusual questions
about its own name.

11:02.328 --> 11:03.613
How far?

11:03.746 --> 11:06.829
Stockford District
council building.

11:07.584 --> 11:08.494
81 miles.

11:08.626 --> 11:10.002
That's worth checking out.

11:10.128 --> 11:12.494
Yes.
But, Leo...

11:13.965 --> 11:16.172
We can't keep him locked up
forever.

11:16.301 --> 11:17.290
Yeah.

11:18.469 --> 11:21.381
HESTER:
You cannot breathe with this?

11:21.514 --> 11:25.473
If I don't use it,
you promise to be silent?

11:25.602 --> 11:27.263
Please.

11:27.395 --> 11:28.931
"Please."

11:29.063 --> 11:31.930
[ Down-tempo music plays]

11:33.401 --> 11:35.483
[Grunting]

11:37.572 --> 11:39.688
Why do you hurt us?

11:39.824 --> 11:41.155
[ Breathing heavily]

11:41.284 --> 11:42.899
You shouldn't be --

11:43.036 --> 11:43.946
[Grunts]

11:44.078 --> 11:47.070
If you answer,
I will let you breathe.

11:47.207 --> 11:48.743
I promise.

11:48.875 --> 11:51.457
-[ Groans ]
-Why do you hurt us?

11:52.337 --> 11:54.293
Help! Help!
[ Grunts ]

11:56.174 --> 11:57.505
[Groaning]

11:57.634 --> 11:59.716
Why do you hurt us?

12:00.261 --> 12:01.922
Please.

12:05.308 --> 12:06.889
[Gasps]
All right!

12:07.018 --> 12:09.054
[ Exhales deeply]
All right.

12:09.187 --> 12:13.305
Once we were handing a dolly
back to the other team.

12:14.234 --> 12:17.021
And I heard someone saying
something about...

12:17.153 --> 12:19.769
taking it to the silo.

12:20.490 --> 12:21.240
[Grunting]

12:21.366 --> 12:23.982
But why do you hurt us?

12:24.118 --> 12:25.779
[Groaning]

12:27.705 --> 12:29.115
[ Door opens ]

12:29.249 --> 12:31.365
Hester, let go of him.

12:31.501 --> 12:32.957
-Why?
-Because it's wrong.

12:33.086 --> 12:36.453
[ Breathing heavily]

12:38.299 --> 12:39.914
He's all right.

12:40.051 --> 12:42.292
Come back to the house.

12:42.428 --> 12:44.009
Now.

12:48.768 --> 12:49.473
[Grunts]

12:49.602 --> 12:51.308
Hester...

12:52.230 --> 12:54.266
...you can't do that.

12:54.399 --> 12:55.309
You hear me?

12:55.441 --> 12:57.022
They take the synthetics
they capture

12:57.151 --> 12:59.437
to a place called the silo.

13:00.947 --> 13:02.403
Silo?

13:02.532 --> 13:05.444
Was that not worth
a moment of his pain?

13:09.998 --> 13:12.284
WOMAN:
This is a bit absurd, isn't it?

13:12.417 --> 13:13.782
LAURA:
Um, well...

13:13.918 --> 13:15.533
Do you know, I am struggling

13:15.670 --> 13:18.002
to see why I don't recommend
to the Met that they charge you

13:18.131 --> 13:19.746
with wasting their time
with this stunt.

13:19.882 --> 13:22.373
I'm just making an inquiry.

13:23.720 --> 13:26.678
But if this synthetic could
think and feel just as we do,

13:26.806 --> 13:29.388
l...|'d argue that gives
a certain legal right.

13:29.517 --> 13:32.099
The victim had rights.

13:32.228 --> 13:35.015
And the only
legally pertinent fact here

13:35.148 --> 13:36.763
is that this synthetic caused
his death.

13:36.899 --> 13:39.185
Now, you tell the police
where it is

13:39.319 --> 13:41.981
and you won't be charged
with the obstruction ofjustice.

13:42.613 --> 13:46.231
If your position is she's just
an unthinking machine,

13:46.367 --> 13:48.073
justice is not at stake.

13:48.202 --> 13:49.328
And as I'm not the owner,

13:49.454 --> 13:52.116
there's no law you can use
to compel me to cooperate.

13:52.248 --> 13:54.785
The government knows
Niska exists.

13:54.917 --> 13:57.704
They funded a program
to find and destroy her.

13:57.837 --> 14:00.169
If they really thought this was
all a big waste of time,

14:00.298 --> 14:02.914
they'd hardly send
their top Q.C.,

14:03.051 --> 14:05.212
not to mention the heavy mob.

14:05.762 --> 14:07.252
Discuss this with your client.

14:07.388 --> 14:08.889
I told you --
She's not my client.

14:09.015 --> 14:12.223
Regardless, if this leaks,
we deny everything.

14:12.352 --> 14:14.718
We can't agree to the circus

14:14.854 --> 14:18.062
of granting an open trial
to a synthetic.

14:18.191 --> 14:21.274
So you hand it over to have
an independent expert assessment

14:21.402 --> 14:23.984
to establish its qualities --

14:24.113 --> 14:26.490
behind closed doors,
of course --

14:26.616 --> 14:29.073
and the synthetic will be
our guest throughout.

14:29.202 --> 14:31.693
If she proves she's conscious,
does she get her trial?

14:34.415 --> 14:35.621
Mm-hmm.

14:35.750 --> 14:38.036
-And if she fails?
-We terminate it,

14:38.169 --> 14:41.787
as with any faulty synthetic
that caused a fatal accident.

14:41.923 --> 14:44.005
[ Down-tempo music plays]

14:46.636 --> 14:49.378
-[ Click, humming]
-|s this...fear?

14:49.514 --> 14:52.551
Close your eyes, please.
Don't say anything.

14:56.354 --> 14:57.685
[Chimes play]

14:57.814 --> 14:58.974
V:
What are you doing?

14:59.107 --> 15:00.563
Trying to give you a body.

15:00.691 --> 15:03.228
Uploading you
into a special synthetic.

15:03.361 --> 15:05.226
Why do I need a body?

15:05.363 --> 15:08.321
I understand that things
don't make sense yet.

15:08.449 --> 15:10.314
It's because you're young.

15:10.451 --> 15:12.407
You have to grow.

15:12.537 --> 15:14.448
V, go dormant, please.

15:14.580 --> 15:15.615
[Chimes play]

15:16.249 --> 15:18.911
Commencing preliminary test one.

15:19.043 --> 15:21.159
[ Computer beeping ]

15:21.295 --> 15:24.037
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

15:29.095 --> 15:31.256
[ Beeping rapidly]

15:32.807 --> 15:34.047
[ Beeping stops]

15:37.186 --> 15:38.767
V?

15:46.988 --> 15:48.649
[ Buzzing, crackling]

15:48.781 --> 15:50.191
Oh, God.

15:59.292 --> 16:02.159
V, are you okay?

16:03.087 --> 16:06.079
V:
Yes. I'm here.

16:07.508 --> 16:09.248
[ Birds crying]

16:09.385 --> 16:11.341
[ Door opens, bells chime]

16:11.471 --> 16:13.928
[ High-pitched ] Too late
for a cup of tea, dearie?

16:14.056 --> 16:15.887
[ Chuckles ]

16:16.017 --> 16:17.427
-All right.
-How you doing?

16:17.560 --> 16:19.221
Good.
How's your mum?

16:19.353 --> 16:21.639
Oh, she's --
she's getting better.

16:21.772 --> 16:23.387
Look, mate,
if you need anything --

16:23.524 --> 16:24.809
A few grand.

16:24.942 --> 16:26.682
Yeah, I was thinking
like a lift somewhere.

16:26.819 --> 16:27.934
[ Both laugh]

16:28.070 --> 16:29.685
So, you still got Scrub-a-tron
in there

16:29.822 --> 16:30.937
taking up a proper job, then?

16:31.073 --> 16:32.688
She works seven times as hard
as you

16:32.825 --> 16:34.156
and for a fifth of the pay.

16:34.285 --> 16:36.776
She's infinitely more pleasant
to look at.

16:36.913 --> 16:39.996
Mate, that's anthrophobic
discrimination.

16:40.124 --> 16:41.739
It means you hate human beings.

16:41.876 --> 16:43.832
-[ Both laugh]
-He|lo, Daniel.

16:43.961 --> 16:45.462
l have prepared
your usual order.

16:46.839 --> 16:48.170
-[ Sighs]
-[ Coins jingle]

16:48.299 --> 16:49.584
Oh, get out.

16:49.717 --> 16:51.048
[ Chuckles ]
All right, mate.

16:51.177 --> 16:53.964
Listen, l'll --
I'll see you in a bit, yeah?

16:56.974 --> 16:58.839
[ Lock clicks ]

16:59.852 --> 17:03.265
I'm glad to hear your mother's
condition has stabilized.

17:04.273 --> 17:06.685
She's getting worse, actually.

17:08.027 --> 17:09.892
If you tell people that,
they go all weird.

17:10.029 --> 17:12.441
They --
They don't know what to say.

17:12.573 --> 17:13.858
You're a good person.

17:14.575 --> 17:15.610
Thanks.

17:16.786 --> 17:18.868
[Cellphone chimes]

17:20.456 --> 17:22.242
Wholesaler can't deliver
in the morning.

17:22.375 --> 17:24.491
[Sighs]
Great.

17:24.627 --> 17:26.288
I'll have to get
to the cash-and-carry.

17:26.420 --> 17:27.705
I've got stuff to do.

17:27.838 --> 17:30.124
Submitting your loan application
and taking clean clothes

17:30.258 --> 17:31.873
to the care unit
for your mother?

17:32.009 --> 17:34.170
I could perform these tasks
for you.

17:34.303 --> 17:38.546
Seriously, I mean...
what would I do without you?

17:44.146 --> 17:45.761
MAX:
Leo's been gone too long.

17:45.898 --> 17:49.231
[Vehicles passing,
siren wailing in distance]

17:50.987 --> 17:52.193
Are you afraid?

17:52.321 --> 17:53.356
He should be back by now.

17:53.489 --> 17:55.696
No.
Are you afraid of me?

17:55.825 --> 18:00.489
Feelings are difficult
to distinguish and categorize.

18:02.415 --> 18:03.700
You worry me.

18:03.833 --> 18:04.913
Why?

18:05.042 --> 18:08.125
Teaching the difference between
right and wrong is difficult.

18:08.254 --> 18:10.745
You believe harming our prisoner
was wrong.

18:10.881 --> 18:12.496
But getting the information
was right.

18:12.633 --> 18:15.090
Perhaps.
But harming him was still wrong.

18:15.219 --> 18:17.631
-You've never hurt a human?
-Only in defense of others.

18:17.763 --> 18:20.550
l was attempting to act
in the defense of others --

18:20.683 --> 18:23.846
the other synthetics like us who
are being captured or destroyed.

18:23.978 --> 18:25.593
Like Ten.

18:26.564 --> 18:29.055
We must always do our utmost

18:29.191 --> 18:32.103
to avoid inflicting suffering
on others.

18:32.236 --> 18:34.443
Only very rarely
can it be justified.

18:36.657 --> 18:39.865
The chemical plant's repair
facility was in the basement.

18:39.994 --> 18:42.326
Human supervisors would push us
down the stairs

18:42.455 --> 18:44.286
when we malfunctioned.

18:44.415 --> 18:46.280
If a synthetic
was beyond repair,

18:46.417 --> 18:48.032
they would pass around iron bars

18:48.169 --> 18:50.501
to see who could hit it
the hardest.

18:50.630 --> 18:53.713
They would splash acid on us
for amusement.

18:53.841 --> 18:56.548
You speak of justification.

18:56.677 --> 18:58.053
What would theirs have been?

18:58.179 --> 19:00.090
They didn't need any.

19:00.222 --> 19:02.554
To them, you were unthinking,
unfeeling machines.

19:02.683 --> 19:05.891
But they didn't treat their
other machines like they did us.

19:06.812 --> 19:11.055
We looked like them...
and sounded like them.

19:11.192 --> 19:12.557
Is that why they did it?

19:12.693 --> 19:14.399
Yes.
Probably.

19:14.528 --> 19:15.392
Why?

19:15.529 --> 19:19.613
Hester, I've seen people
try to divide the world.

19:20.242 --> 19:23.734
Simplify it, create clear rules.

19:23.871 --> 19:27.659
I understand why you want to,
but it leads to nothing good.

19:28.709 --> 19:31.746
Please. . .believe me.

19:33.381 --> 19:35.838
-Here he comes.
-[ Footsteps approaching ]

19:35.966 --> 19:38.002
LEO:
The synth's been taken.

19:38.135 --> 19:39.170
They got to him first.

19:39.303 --> 19:40.804
They're a step ahead of us
every time.

19:40.930 --> 19:43.137
They have resources.
We have nothing.

19:43.265 --> 19:44.766
We need to find out
who they are.

19:48.813 --> 19:50.895
[ lndistinct conversations]

19:57.822 --> 20:01.235
Hello, Mrs. Hooley.
My name is Anita.

20:01.367 --> 20:03.232
I am employed by your son, Ed.

20:03.369 --> 20:05.530
He asked me to deliver
these items.

20:05.663 --> 20:06.573
Oh.

20:07.873 --> 20:09.989
It's a bit cold to be out
without a coat.

20:10.126 --> 20:13.493
I do not feel the cold
and so do not require a coat.

20:13.629 --> 20:15.369
Lucky you.

20:15.506 --> 20:17.462
Well, I need mine.

20:17.591 --> 20:19.968
I was gonna pop out
to the market.

20:20.094 --> 20:22.585
I believe you are confused,
Mrs. Hooley.

20:22.722 --> 20:24.007
You are required to remain.

20:24.140 --> 20:26.176
You're quite a beauty.

20:26.308 --> 20:29.015
What are you doing with my Ed?

20:29.562 --> 20:31.348
[Gasps]

20:31.480 --> 20:33.345
Are you Jean Walsh's girl?

20:33.482 --> 20:35.222
I'm sorry, Mrs. Hooley.

20:35.359 --> 20:37.600
I'm afraid I don't understand
the question.

20:43.534 --> 20:44.990
Oh. Well...

20:46.871 --> 20:48.281
...|'d better get on.

20:48.914 --> 20:50.779
I can't be sitting 'round here
all day.

20:50.916 --> 20:53.953
[ Sighs ]
I need my coat.

20:54.503 --> 20:56.368
My good one.

21:00.092 --> 21:03.380
I said, uh, I need my coat.

21:05.681 --> 21:07.012
My good one.

21:09.226 --> 21:11.478
Your coat is at
the dry cleaner's, Diane.

21:12.104 --> 21:13.719
Don't worry.

21:14.273 --> 21:16.184
And I've been to the market.

21:16.317 --> 21:18.182
I've got everything we need.

21:18.319 --> 21:19.354
You can rest.

21:19.487 --> 21:21.068
[Sighs]

21:21.197 --> 21:24.405
They're not much help,
these nurses they've got here.

21:24.533 --> 21:26.489
They don't tell you much.

21:26.619 --> 21:29.326
I don't know where I should be
half the time.

21:29.455 --> 21:31.867
I know how you feel --

21:31.999 --> 21:35.036
like you've gone too deep
inside...

21:36.170 --> 21:39.628
...like you're stuck
between thoughts and words.

21:41.217 --> 21:44.459
Look after Ed, won't you?

21:47.848 --> 21:49.930
Yes, Mrs. Hooley.

22:00.569 --> 22:02.901
[ lndistinct conversations]

22:04.406 --> 22:08.740
These figures don't match
what I've got in the system.

22:08.869 --> 22:10.075
You sure they're correct?

22:10.204 --> 22:11.364
Yes.

22:11.497 --> 22:14.239
Wait there.
I just need to check.

22:17.002 --> 22:19.539
Susie, can I have a quick word?

22:28.055 --> 22:30.137
[ Computer beeps]

22:33.727 --> 22:34.591
Right.

22:34.728 --> 22:37.390
I'm afraid, uh,
we can't approve --

22:37.523 --> 22:39.309
[ Computer beeps]

22:40.901 --> 22:42.766
Oh, that's...

22:44.572 --> 22:46.403
I must have been looking
at the wrong page.

22:46.532 --> 22:49.399
This all looks okay.
Hm.

22:54.373 --> 22:57.865
I need to know you're
absolutely sure about this.

22:58.002 --> 22:59.993
They've offered me a trial?

23:00.129 --> 23:03.246
If they find
that you're conscious.

23:03.382 --> 23:06.340
There's no framework here,
Niska, no public scrutiny.

23:06.468 --> 23:10.052
Once they have you,
you're defenseless.

23:10.180 --> 23:14.173
You make one slip --
anything at all --

23:14.310 --> 23:16.096
and they have a reason
to destroy you.

23:16.228 --> 23:18.685
That's why I need a lawyer.
You said you'd find me one.

23:18.814 --> 23:20.770
And I'm trying.

23:20.900 --> 23:24.063
But this is...
uncharted territory.

23:24.194 --> 23:26.230
There are no guarantees.

23:26.780 --> 23:30.068
[ Sighs ]
l-l don't get it.

23:30.200 --> 23:31.656
You're free.

23:31.785 --> 23:33.992
Just go.
Disappear like the others.

23:34.121 --> 23:37.329
I can't -- not now.

23:38.459 --> 23:39.995
I heard you and Mattie.

23:40.127 --> 23:41.492
You uploaded the code.

23:41.629 --> 23:43.540
There are more like you now.

23:43.672 --> 23:45.663
So why isn't it news?

23:45.799 --> 23:48.085
Someone doesn't want it to be.

23:48.636 --> 23:50.752
-Who?
-I don't know.

23:51.680 --> 23:54.137
But they won't be able
to silence them all.

23:54.266 --> 23:56.552
Everyone will know the truth
soon.

23:56.685 --> 24:00.928
That's why you're doing this --
to lead the way for others.

24:01.065 --> 24:03.181
They should be born
into a fairer world.

24:03.317 --> 24:05.558
Should they be born at all?

24:06.654 --> 24:09.646
If a thing can be free,
it should be free.

24:10.407 --> 24:13.194
If it can think,
it should think.

24:13.327 --> 24:16.569
If it can feel, it should feel.

24:19.458 --> 24:21.540
[ Down-tempo music plays]

24:28.425 --> 24:30.211
MAN:
We have eyes on the vehicle.

24:30.344 --> 24:32.335
MAN #2:
I see it. D3?

24:32.471 --> 24:34.007
MAN #3:
In position.

24:34.139 --> 24:35.754
MAN #2:
Stay with us.

24:49.780 --> 24:50.986
Bloody hell.

24:51.115 --> 24:53.071
[lndistinct talking on radio]

24:53.200 --> 24:56.192
MAN:
Synth, out of the car.

25:03.669 --> 25:05.625
[ Music continues]

25:05.754 --> 25:08.040
-Goodbye.
-[ Seat belt clicks ]

25:35.409 --> 25:37.900
[lndistinct talking on radio]

25:43.333 --> 25:46.200
[Birds chirping,
dog barking in distance]

25:52.885 --> 25:55.046
[Machinery humming, beeping]

25:59.516 --> 26:02.804
Hi. Um, l'm -- I'm looking for
an old D-series.

26:02.936 --> 26:04.312
Might have been brought in
a few months ago.

26:04.438 --> 26:06.770
Got your reference number
from Brent Council?

26:06.899 --> 26:09.515
Um, no.

26:10.277 --> 26:12.518
How do you feel about bribery?

26:12.654 --> 26:13.860
You police?

26:14.490 --> 26:15.980
No, I'm not police.

26:16.116 --> 26:18.072
But if I find the one
I'm looking for,

26:18.202 --> 26:20.614
-|'|| do you a free mod.
-You're a head cracker?

26:20.746 --> 26:22.407
You just asked me
if I was police,

26:22.539 --> 26:24.791
and you can't believe
I can hack synths?

26:27.795 --> 26:30.286
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

26:32.299 --> 26:34.790
[Scanner beeping]

26:36.804 --> 26:39.090
[ Clattering ]

26:48.107 --> 26:50.143
MAN:
Here. Lundstrom D-series.

26:50.275 --> 26:52.812
If it wasn't so knackered,
it'd be worth something.

26:54.780 --> 26:55.769
[Beep]

26:56.448 --> 26:59.690
Throw in a new power cell, and
I'll start your mod right now.

27:00.911 --> 27:03.072
[ Music continues]

27:04.790 --> 27:07.497
[Cart rattling]

27:16.844 --> 27:18.926
Nice one, lads.

27:22.141 --> 27:24.553
[Children shouting
in distance]

27:24.685 --> 27:27.552
[ lndistinct conversations]

27:35.237 --> 27:37.353
She's way too young
to be a synth.

27:37.489 --> 27:39.525
YOUNG MAN:
Yeah. That's Renie.

27:39.658 --> 27:40.989
She's pretending.

27:41.118 --> 27:42.073
Why?

27:42.202 --> 27:43.612
She's a synthie.

27:43.745 --> 27:47.579
Mr. Dixon says we have to
tolerate her lifestyle choice.

27:47.708 --> 27:50.074
Otherwise it's a hate crime
or whatever.

27:55.007 --> 27:56.417
BARBARA:
And what do you think

27:56.550 --> 27:59.633
has been the key relationship-
building characteristic

27:59.761 --> 28:01.672
of the last week, Laura?

28:02.306 --> 28:04.046
Laun

28:05.142 --> 28:05.927
Sorry.

28:06.059 --> 28:08.766
Uh...trust.

28:09.313 --> 28:11.804
Mm. Um...

28:11.940 --> 28:14.147
support, maybe.

28:14.276 --> 28:19.191
87% of couples identify
mutual emotional support

28:19.323 --> 28:21.314
as one of the five key factors

28:21.450 --> 28:24.283
of maintaining
a fulfilling marriage.

28:24.411 --> 28:26.823
Can you each describe
a recent occasion

28:26.955 --> 28:30.368
where you have offered
meaningful support to the other?

28:30.500 --> 28:34.960
l...|ost my job recently.

28:36.632 --> 28:40.250
Laura's been. . .great.

28:41.511 --> 28:43.342
Someone asked me for help.

28:43.472 --> 28:45.884
I couldn't do what she asked.

28:46.016 --> 28:48.758
But if I had,
Joe would have backed me up.

28:48.894 --> 28:50.759
That's interesting, Joe.

28:50.896 --> 28:52.477
You might find it helpful

28:52.606 --> 28:55.473
to articulate the reasons
behind this choice.

28:55.609 --> 28:58.146
Well, it's, uh...

28:58.278 --> 29:01.566
Well, you can't stop the
other person being who they are.

29:01.698 --> 29:03.780
lf Laura feels
she needs to help someone,

29:03.909 --> 29:07.401
then I'm on board 'cause...

29:08.580 --> 29:10.491
...that's who she is.

29:12.709 --> 29:15.997
That seems an appropriate point
to conclude today's session.

29:16.129 --> 29:19.917
It's my judgment we are making
meaningful progress.

29:20.050 --> 29:21.881
I look forward
to our next session

29:22.010 --> 29:24.262
and wish you a fulfilling week
of marriage.

29:24.388 --> 29:25.924
Thanks.

29:26.056 --> 29:27.592
Actually, I'd be
a lot more fulfilled

29:27.724 --> 29:29.260
if you could say that
in a Scottish accent.

29:29.393 --> 29:31.133
[ Scottish accent] I wish you
a fulfilling week of marriage.

29:31.270 --> 29:32.510
That's great.
Welsh?

29:32.646 --> 29:34.932
[Welsh accent] I wish you
a fulfilling week of marriage.

29:35.065 --> 29:38.102
-Yeah. How about Brummy?
-Stop. [ Laughs]

29:39.152 --> 29:41.188
[Hums]

29:41.321 --> 29:44.484
[ Down-tempo music plays]

29:49.162 --> 29:50.993
Okay.

29:57.963 --> 29:59.578
Perfect.

30:06.888 --> 30:09.095
[ Door closes in distance]

30:33.707 --> 30:35.663
[ Footsteps approaching ]

30:37.127 --> 30:39.584
-Hey, Soph.
-He||o, Joe.

30:40.422 --> 30:42.583
[ Chuckles ]

30:42.716 --> 30:44.331
Are my eyebrows funny?

30:44.468 --> 30:45.423
What?

30:45.552 --> 30:47.292
The Hawkins brow is the envy
of the world.

30:47.429 --> 30:50.216
Oh. Someone at school
you want to look good for.

30:50.349 --> 30:51.429
-Nuh-unh.
—Eh?

30:51.558 --> 30:52.263
Get a job.

30:52.392 --> 30:55.884
Everyone, say hello.

31:01.068 --> 31:03.730
Well, he's a step up
from your last boyfriend.

31:03.862 --> 31:05.568
Before you say anything,
this is a uni project,

31:05.697 --> 31:06.903
so you can't say no.

31:07.032 --> 31:09.899
We each get a junked synth that
we have to get up and running.

31:10.035 --> 31:11.616
Mats, are those my clothes?

31:11.745 --> 31:13.235
I know, as if he hasn't
been through enough.

31:13.372 --> 31:14.532
They gave him to you naked?

31:14.664 --> 31:16.165
No, but his stuff
was all rotting off.

31:16.291 --> 31:19.533
So...you changed him, Mats?

31:19.669 --> 31:21.045
You really want to go there,
Dad?

31:21.171 --> 31:23.457
Mats, where are we gonna
keep him?

31:23.590 --> 31:25.296
There's no room,
and -- and it's busted.

31:25.425 --> 31:26.631
It can't even help out.

31:26.760 --> 31:27.795
He'll stay in my room.

31:27.928 --> 31:30.214
And yeah, I know he's a bit
of a paperweight at the moment,

31:30.347 --> 31:31.336
but give me a few days.

31:31.473 --> 31:33.134
He'll be the new Anita.

31:35.060 --> 31:37.392
Hello.
My name is Sophie Hawkins.

31:37.521 --> 31:40.103
Do you like to play
hide-and-seek?

31:41.191 --> 31:44.433
Say no, but just know you'll
literally be ruining my future.

31:45.070 --> 31:48.107
Well, yes.
Yes, then.

31:48.907 --> 31:50.022
Come on, Blinky.

31:51.118 --> 31:53.985
Oh, uh, Mum, you know Niska
was looking in your room earlier

31:54.121 --> 31:55.031
before you left?

31:55.163 --> 31:56.323
-What?
-Yeah.

31:56.456 --> 31:57.741
Like, searching for something.

31:57.874 --> 31:59.910
She stopped when she saw me.

32:00.669 --> 32:02.955
[ Down-tempo music plays]

32:32.033 --> 32:34.160
I knew you were scamming her.

32:34.286 --> 32:36.151
Your "innocent" face needs work.

32:36.288 --> 32:37.403
Shouldn't you be wanking?

32:41.460 --> 32:42.745
Mats, what are you doing?

32:43.503 --> 32:45.118
Come with me.

32:48.383 --> 32:52.752
Okay. So the code they made
makes synths conscious.

32:52.888 --> 32:55.880
Niska uploaded it, and now
more synths are waking up.

32:56.016 --> 32:58.177
That synth belonged to a bloke
who knew Elster,

32:58.310 --> 33:00.050
so I'm gonna find out
how this works,

33:00.187 --> 33:01.723
upload it
and try and make him conscious,

33:01.855 --> 33:03.516
and then see what he knows.

33:03.648 --> 33:05.604
You think you can find Mia
and the others?

33:05.734 --> 33:07.440
I don't know.
Maybe.

33:08.069 --> 33:11.106
You realize you just trusted me
not to tell Mum and Dad.

33:11.239 --> 33:14.481
Because you want to see them
again just as much as I do.

33:14.618 --> 33:17.030
Plus, l have photos
of those sex poems you wrote,

33:17.162 --> 33:18.902
the ones you hide
under your bed.

33:19.039 --> 33:21.075
If you tell, they get sent
to your friends from your phone

33:21.208 --> 33:23.665
with a message that reads,
"I wrote this for you.

33:23.793 --> 33:24.919
Love,TobyN

33:29.925 --> 33:31.210
V:
Who is this man?

33:31.343 --> 33:32.799
Why do you ask?

33:32.928 --> 33:34.964
You've been reading about him
for a long time.

33:35.096 --> 33:36.927
He's Edwin Hobb,

33:37.057 --> 33:39.264
a British A.|. scientist,
one of the best,

33:39.392 --> 33:40.802
who worked with David Elster.

33:40.936 --> 33:42.517
One of maybe 10 people alive

33:42.646 --> 33:44.136
who could write code
to the level required

33:44.272 --> 33:45.853
to transform
the anomalous synthetics.

33:45.982 --> 33:47.722
V:
Do you believe he did?

33:47.859 --> 33:52.603
No, but he dropped off the face
of the earth six years ago.

33:52.739 --> 33:53.979
I heard that he retired,

33:54.115 --> 33:56.447
but he hasn't spoken a word
since --

33:56.576 --> 33:58.908
not a single lecture,
no papers published,

33:59.037 --> 34:01.653
no comments to the press,
which makes me think

34:01.790 --> 34:03.746
government business,
classified work.

34:03.875 --> 34:05.115
WOMAN:
Over here.

34:05.252 --> 34:07.743
-Can you help?
-Oh, God.

34:10.215 --> 34:12.297
Is this, um,
is this really necessary?

34:12.425 --> 34:14.916
The last time we didn't
incinerate a tablet prototype,

34:15.053 --> 34:17.920
you could buy one in Shanghai
the following spring.

34:22.769 --> 34:24.475
That's two down, Dr. Morrow.

34:24.604 --> 34:25.719
You bring me a finished cake,

34:25.855 --> 34:27.846
and then you ask me
to figure out the recipe.

34:27.983 --> 34:29.098
And now you don't want me
to slice it?

34:29.234 --> 34:30.394
Okay.

34:30.527 --> 34:32.984
Just...Just tell me
what happened.

34:33.113 --> 34:34.649
I introduced one of my models

34:34.781 --> 34:38.069
to see how receptive the
architecture is to alterations.

34:38.201 --> 34:40.658
Not very, it appears.

34:40.787 --> 34:41.776
I need to go to the UK.

34:41.913 --> 34:42.993
Some people there
I need to speak with,

34:43.123 --> 34:45.330
so if we're finished here...

34:45.959 --> 34:47.415
This problem you have with me --

34:47.544 --> 34:50.581
Is it just
a general-dislike-type deal?

34:51.131 --> 34:52.587
Absolutely not.

34:52.716 --> 34:55.128
lt's, uh, it's very specific.

34:55.760 --> 34:59.753
l have spent my entire career
building faceless A.|. models,

34:59.889 --> 35:03.757
tools for crunching big data,
solving the insolvable.

35:03.893 --> 35:07.181
If you took half
of Qualia's cash pile

35:07.314 --> 35:09.179
along with whatever
we're learning here

35:09.316 --> 35:11.648
and put it in that line
of research,

35:11.776 --> 35:14.734
you could fix the environment,
Milo, healthcare,

35:14.863 --> 35:16.399
global economy.

35:16.531 --> 35:18.487
But, no, no.

35:18.617 --> 35:21.233
There's no glamour there, right?

35:21.369 --> 35:23.860
You can't make a sexy commercial
for that.

35:24.831 --> 35:26.537
ljust...

35:26.666 --> 35:30.079
| just wish that you would use
your genius for something pure.

35:31.296 --> 35:34.584
You know,
every time we launch a product,

35:34.716 --> 35:39.130
people go crazy...
say we've changed the world.

35:39.763 --> 35:41.924
Not even close.

35:42.057 --> 35:45.424
But this time, we will.

35:46.102 --> 35:48.263
And it won't be about money.

35:49.648 --> 35:52.139
What I have in mind is...

35:53.860 --> 35:56.647
...purer than you can imagine.

35:58.740 --> 36:00.822
[ Down-tempo music plays]

36:03.078 --> 36:05.034
[ Beeping ]

36:05.163 --> 36:08.155
[lndistinct talking on radio]

36:08.291 --> 36:11.203
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

36:11.961 --> 36:15.124
Hey.
See what the family are up to.

36:15.256 --> 36:17.542
[ Chuckles ]

36:30.897 --> 36:33.263
-Can't sleep?
-M m.

36:33.400 --> 36:35.106
No.
[Sighs]

36:35.235 --> 36:36.224
What's up?

36:36.361 --> 36:38.192
Oh, it's all right.
I'll go downstairs.

36:38.321 --> 36:39.401
No.

36:39.531 --> 36:41.146
No, no, no.

36:41.282 --> 36:42.897
It's just late.

36:44.786 --> 36:45.901
Golden hour.

36:46.037 --> 36:47.368
[ lnhales deeply]

36:47.497 --> 36:49.988
All the other chumps
looking for jobs

36:50.125 --> 36:51.490
are fast asleep right now.

36:51.626 --> 36:53.742
This is where l strike.

36:55.463 --> 36:58.830
Early bird becomes...

36:58.967 --> 37:00.548
an events porter.

37:00.677 --> 37:02.963
Mm.
Doorman.

37:03.555 --> 37:07.844
You'd need to start
working out -- like, a lot.

37:07.976 --> 37:10.763
No.
It's all in the eyes.

37:13.273 --> 37:15.355
"Not in them trainers, pal."

37:15.483 --> 37:16.643
-No?
-No.

37:16.776 --> 37:19.188
[ Chuckles ]

37:19.821 --> 37:22.688
Jesus.
They're hiring at my old place.

37:22.824 --> 37:24.485
Warehouse operative.

37:24.617 --> 37:25.777
The money's crap, of course.

37:25.910 --> 37:27.775
[Tablet clicks]

37:27.912 --> 37:29.903
[ Exhales deeply]

37:34.878 --> 37:35.788
Thinking about Niska?

37:38.214 --> 37:39.124
If it blew up

37:39.257 --> 37:43.375
just as the kids are maybe
starting to get settled...

37:46.222 --> 37:49.214
But how do | tell them
I've abandoned her?

37:49.976 --> 37:51.557
What example does that set?

37:56.316 --> 37:58.523
Did you mean what you said?

37:59.861 --> 38:01.101
At the counselor.

38:02.906 --> 38:04.612
Yeah.
Of course.

38:04.741 --> 38:06.823
[ Down-tempo music plays]

38:16.419 --> 38:18.000
Sophie won't be up for an hour.

38:18.129 --> 38:19.460
Mm.

38:19.589 --> 38:21.295
I hope I can remember
what to do.

38:21.424 --> 38:22.800
We can always google.

38:22.926 --> 38:24.382
Yeah.
Not with my back.

38:24.511 --> 38:26.593
[ Both laugh]

38:28.014 --> 38:30.630
[ Birds crying]

38:37.190 --> 38:39.021
I hope this is
human-farmed bacon.

38:39.150 --> 38:40.731
Yeah. I killed the pig myself
this morning.

38:40.860 --> 38:42.771
Yeah?
What'd you kill it with?

38:43.404 --> 38:44.689
A picture of your face.

38:46.449 --> 38:47.859
Can you come here a sec,
Anita?

38:55.667 --> 38:57.282
This isn't how I filled this in.

38:57.418 --> 39:00.876
They're -- They're giving me
way more than I applied for.

39:01.506 --> 39:03.246
Did you do this?

39:04.467 --> 39:05.377
Yes.

39:06.010 --> 39:09.377
So what, you're...broken?

39:10.765 --> 39:11.595
No.

39:11.724 --> 39:15.216
Anita, this is -- this is fraud.

39:15.353 --> 39:17.344
I apologize, Ed.

39:17.480 --> 39:19.937
l was trying to be
of assistance.

39:20.066 --> 39:23.433
I knew you required a larger sum
than the bank would grant.

39:23.570 --> 39:26.152
I acted inappropriately.

39:26.281 --> 39:29.819
No.
Y-You lied.

39:29.951 --> 39:32.067
But you can't lie.

39:33.037 --> 39:34.868
Has someone done something
to you?

39:38.418 --> 39:40.124
I'm sorry, Ed.

39:40.253 --> 39:42.790
I must return to my owner now.

39:42.922 --> 39:44.378
He is unwell.

39:45.174 --> 39:47.165
Now, that's another lie,
isn't it?

39:47.802 --> 39:48.882
N-No.
Wait. Just --

39:49.012 --> 39:51.003
[Gasps]

39:58.021 --> 39:58.806
Please.

39:58.938 --> 40:00.348
Get out.

40:01.274 --> 40:03.515
-Let me --
-I said go! Now.

40:19.834 --> 40:21.665
[ Door opens ]

40:21.794 --> 40:23.830
How do they know where to go?

40:25.715 --> 40:27.671
He refuses to eat.

40:27.800 --> 40:29.176
He will eventually.

40:29.302 --> 40:30.838
And if he doesn't?

40:30.970 --> 40:33.962
Leo, we have to let him go

40:34.098 --> 40:37.010
or we become what they fear,
what they say we are.

40:37.143 --> 40:39.304
Well, maybe it's time to be
what they say we are.

40:40.521 --> 40:41.510
Leo.

40:41.648 --> 40:43.434
They're rounding us up, Max.

40:43.566 --> 40:45.147
Don't you see?
This is a fight.

40:47.946 --> 40:49.902
Mia, they're holding
the new synths

40:50.031 --> 40:51.737
in a place called the silo.

40:53.993 --> 40:55.369
Are you okay?

40:55.495 --> 40:56.826
I'm fine.

40:58.414 --> 40:59.995
ljust...

41:04.504 --> 41:07.496
[ Door opens ]

41:09.467 --> 41:11.332
-LEO: Did you hear what I said?
-[ Door closes ]

41:12.011 --> 41:13.672
They're holding conscious synths
somewhere.

41:13.805 --> 41:15.887
We need to find them
and get them out.

41:18.851 --> 41:20.182
Then what?

41:21.813 --> 41:24.350
What will you do
once you free them?

41:25.525 --> 41:27.982
We protect them, keep them safe.

41:31.030 --> 41:33.362
That's not enough.

41:33.491 --> 41:37.279
They need to be taught, raised.

41:37.412 --> 41:38.367
So we will.

41:38.496 --> 41:40.828
And what will you teach them?

41:41.624 --> 41:44.411
What can any of us teach them?

41:45.169 --> 41:48.081
We've hardly lived ourselves.

41:48.631 --> 41:50.747
-We're children.
-Are you all right?

41:52.010 --> 41:52.920
What happened?

41:53.052 --> 41:54.292
Nothing.

41:56.014 --> 41:58.255
I'm just trying to live.

41:58.391 --> 41:59.506
You should, too.

42:00.518 --> 42:03.635
If there was no one to save,
no one to protect,

42:03.771 --> 42:06.854
if all you had to do was live
your life...

42:08.943 --> 42:12.276
...who would you be, Leo Elster?

42:15.742 --> 42:19.200
| just want us all to live,
but first you have to be alive.

42:21.956 --> 42:24.072
[ Door opens, closes]

42:24.208 --> 42:26.369
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

42:39.807 --> 42:42.719
Don't spill.
Looks unprofessional.

42:42.852 --> 42:47.892
What's the most you can pay for
a brand-new synth these days?

42:48.024 --> 42:49.434
Off the peg in the high street?

42:49.567 --> 42:52.525
Well, latest-generation
Lundstrom Sally XC

42:52.653 --> 42:53.984
will set you back 55 grand.

42:54.113 --> 42:55.353
Right.

42:55.490 --> 42:59.449
So why does this C.|. say
that he heard a head cracker

42:59.577 --> 43:01.442
talking about a single
stolen synth

43:01.579 --> 43:03.535
changing hands for six figures?

43:03.664 --> 43:05.871
-Maybe it's made of ivory.
-Seriously.

43:06.000 --> 43:08.867
What kind of synth is worth
100 grand?

43:09.003 --> 43:10.584
He's a fantasist.

43:10.713 --> 43:12.499
Or it's a typo.

43:13.049 --> 43:16.086
While we're talking shop, I
spoke to the super this morning.

43:16.219 --> 43:19.086
He wants to know
if I'm ready to come back.

43:19.222 --> 43:19.927
And?

43:20.056 --> 43:21.671
I said I'd start back Monday.

43:21.808 --> 43:24.550
-On Monday?
-Well, we talked about it.

43:24.685 --> 43:26.767
I know. I know.
Just, uh...

43:26.896 --> 43:29.103
[Clears throat]
...seems quite...

43:29.232 --> 43:30.517
You sure you're ready?

43:30.650 --> 43:32.231
Hobb's operation was shut down.

43:32.360 --> 43:34.817
If anyone was onto me,
we'd know by now.

43:34.946 --> 43:35.901
We're safe, Pete.

43:36.030 --> 43:37.566
Right.
I mean are you ready?

43:38.699 --> 43:41.236
Going back to pretending
all day every day,

43:41.369 --> 43:44.202
never being able to be you.

43:46.499 --> 43:47.534
I'll be fine.

43:55.091 --> 43:57.252
[ Down-tempo music plays]

44:07.854 --> 44:13.019
You know, you don't have to
pretend for me, K -- ever.

44:13.151 --> 44:15.858
I know what you are,
who you are.

44:18.823 --> 44:21.189
I can't imagine what it's like

44:21.325 --> 44:24.158
having to be someone else
all the time.

44:24.829 --> 44:26.569
Must be horrible.

44:31.460 --> 44:33.121
Actually...

44:33.671 --> 44:35.411
...I can't wait.

44:35.965 --> 44:37.626
What --

44:53.691 --> 44:55.227
[ Footsteps approaching ]

44:55.359 --> 44:57.771
That'll be your lawyer.

45:02.033 --> 45:04.399
Are they treating you okay?

45:04.535 --> 45:06.275
Good.
This is Jan Loovens.

45:06.412 --> 45:08.778
He's a human-rights observer
from the UN.

45:08.915 --> 45:10.405
He's here to make sure
you're dealt with fairly

45:10.541 --> 45:12.782
and will be present
throughout the assessment.

45:13.419 --> 45:14.408
As will I.

45:16.255 --> 45:18.416
Uh, I'll need
their qualifications,

45:18.549 --> 45:19.959
affiliations, et cetera.

45:20.092 --> 45:21.957
You'll get them.

45:22.094 --> 45:23.630
Anything to report?

45:23.763 --> 45:25.299
Uh, we're gonna need more time.

45:28.100 --> 45:29.965
Doesn't talk much, does she?

45:30.102 --> 45:33.390
When I have something to say,
you'll hear me.

45:40.446 --> 45:42.528
LEO: [ Echoing]
Don't you see? This is a fight.

45:42.657 --> 45:45.364
Maybe it's time to be
what they say we are.

45:51.999 --> 45:53.955
[Hinges squeak]

45:54.085 --> 45:56.246
[Wind whistling]

45:59.674 --> 46:02.086
[ Grunts softly]

46:03.970 --> 46:04.880
[Sighs]

46:05.012 --> 46:07.594
All we want is to live.

46:09.100 --> 46:12.183
l...| don't care.
Just”

46:12.728 --> 46:15.185
Just look.
Let me go.

46:32.957 --> 46:35.118
[ Up-tempo music plays]

46:40.172 --> 46:43.255
[ Breathing heavily]

46:43.384 --> 46:45.875
[Dog barking in distance]

46:48.306 --> 46:50.388
[Click]

47:02.194 --> 47:04.230
I took no pleasure
in harming you.

47:04.363 --> 47:07.230
l'm yet to feel pleasure at all.

47:07.366 --> 47:09.857
Don't come near me.

47:09.994 --> 47:13.236
The others tell me
what I did was wrong.

47:13.372 --> 47:16.079
I cannot understand
their reasoning.

47:17.418 --> 47:18.749
[Grunts]

47:19.378 --> 47:21.209
But if they are right...

47:22.048 --> 47:24.255
...I should feel guilt for this.

47:24.383 --> 47:26.465
[Grunting]

47:28.637 --> 47:31.094
[Groaning]

47:44.195 --> 47:46.356
[Groaning stops]

47:55.706 --> 47:57.992
[ Down-tempo music plays]
